#1
Summary: Sign up a new user

Preconditions:
1. Open https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/

Steps:
1. Create and enter unique username into "Username" field
2. Enter your email into "Email" field
3. Create and enter a password into "Password" field (Password must be at least 12 characters)
4. Click [Sign up for OurApp] button

Expected Results:
1. Entered Username displays in "Username" field without error
2. Entered Email displays in "Email" field
3. Password displays in "Password" field as encrypted text (dots) without error
4. Account has been created successfully, welcoming page appears with text "Hello <username>, your feed is empty.",
   username displays on page header next to buttons [Create Post] and [Sign Out]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#2
Summary: Sign out as logged-in user

Preconditions:
1. Log in on https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/ with existing account

Steps:
1. Review page https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/
2. Click [Sign Out]

Expected Results:
1. Correct Username displayed on page header next to buttons [Create Post] and [Sign Out]
2. Page has been reloaded, https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/ opened, form for signing up displayed,
   page header contains: input fields "Username" and "Password", button [Sign In]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#3
Summary: Sign In with existing account

Preconditions:
1. Open https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/
2. User isn't logged in

Steps:
1. Enter valid username into "Username" filed on page header
2. Enter valid password into "Password" field on page header, next to "Username" field
3. Click [Sign In] button

Expected Results:
1. Entered username displays in "Username" field
2. Entered password displays as dots
3. Page has been reloaded, welcoming page appears with text which contains "Hello <username>",
   username displays on page header next to buttons [Create Post] and [Sign Out]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#4
Summary: Create a new public, non-unique post as logged-in user

Preconditions:
1. Open https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/
2. Log in with existing account

Steps:
1. Click [Create Post] button on page header
2. Create and enter post title into "Title" field
3. Enter post text into "Body Content" field
   (e.g. "Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry.")
4. Leave "Is this post unique?" unchecked
5. Leave "Select value" with value "Public"
6. Click [Save New Post]

Expected Results:
1. Page https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/create-post opened.
   The page contains:
   - input fields: Title, Body Content
   - checkbox "Is this post unique?"
   - drop-down "Select value"
   - button [Save New Post]
2. Entered title displays in "Title" field
3. Entered post text displays in "Body Content" field
4. "Is this post unique?" unchecked
5. Drop-down "Select value" has value "Public"
6. Link was changed to https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/post/<created_post_id>
   Page contains the next entities:
   - Text "New post successfully created." with green background
   - Correct title
   - Correct info about post author - current user ("Postred by <username> on <date>")
   - "Is this post unique? : no"
   - Correct post text
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#5
Summary: Change existing, public, non-unique post to unique

Preconditions:
1. Open https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/
2. Log in with existing account
3. Create public, non-unique post

Steps:
1. Open https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/
2. Click "My Profile" button next to username on page header
3. Open created post via clicking on its title
4. Click [Edit] button
5. Check "Is this post unique?"
6. Click [Save Updates]

Expected Results:
1. Page https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/ is opened
2. Link was changed to https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/profile/<username>
   Page contains correct username, tabs "Posts: <n>", "Followers: <n>", "Following: <n>" with correct numbers <n>
   Tab Posts contains public, non-unique post
3. Link was changed to https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/post/<clicked_post_id>
   Page shows correct post
4. Link was changed to https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/post/<clicked_post_id>/edit
   Post editor is opened
5. "Is this post unique?" is checked
6. Post was successfully edited, text "Post successfully updated." displayed with green background
